        public void createTesterUserAndTestingTopic()
        This method is called before each test. Calls method createTestedUser which adds testedUser into the database.

      • dropUser

        public void dropUser()
        This method is called after each test. Calls method dropUser which drops testedUser from database.

      • doesMethodAddUserWork

        public void doesMethodAddUserWork()
        Checks if specific user was created earlier under "@Before" annotation. Checks if String value of userName after calling getPresentUser method equals to String "tester", asserting equal.

      • doesMethodApproveUserWork

        public void doesMethodApproveUserWork()
        Checks two Strings, one string before calling method approveUser and another one after calling method approveUser. Values should change from "pending" to "confirmed".

      • doesMethodIsDBEmptyWork

        public void doesMethodIsDBEmptyWork()
        Checks if the calling of the method isDBEmpty returns false, after creating items in the database before.

      • doesMethodRegisterUserWork

        public void doesMethodRegisterUserWork()
        Calling methods doesMethodAddUserWork and doesMethodSetPresentUserWork, asserting returning true both.

      • doesMethodChangePasswordWorks

        public void doesMethodChangePasswordWorks()
        Checks two Strings, one string before calling method changePassword and another one after calling method changePassword. Values should not be the same when compared.

      • doesMethodIsPasswordCorrectWork

        public void doesMethodIsPasswordCorrectWork()
        Compares two String values with the value of password stored in the database for specified user. First compared same String as stored, asserting true, second compared different String as stored, asserting false.

      • deosMethodIsUserApprovedWork

        public void deosMethodIsUserApprovedWork()
        Checks if is user "tester" has status equal to "confirmed", asserting not true.

      • doesMethodGetUserIDWork

        public void doesMethodGetUserIDWork()
        Checks two userID of type integer, one stored as 0 and another stored in database, asserting that they do not equal.

      • doesMethodGetPresentUserWork

        public void doesMethodGetPresentUserWork()
        Checks two userName of type String, one stored as "tester" and another stored in database, retrieved by calling method getPresentUser, asserting that they do equal.

      • doesMethodGetPendingUsersWork

        public void doesMethodGetPendingUsersWork()
        Comparing two lists, one created by calling method getPendingUsers before adding user "testingDummy" into database and second created by calling the same method after adding the user. Expecting that lists do not equal. Calling method dropUser on user "testingDummy" at the end.

      • doesMethodDropUserWork

        public void doesMethodDropUserWork()
        Checks if user "testingDummy" is in table after calling dropUse method, expecting null

      • doesMethodUpdateImageWork

        public void doesMethodUpdateImageWork()
        Checks the profileImage of selected user before and after calling method updateImage. Before expecting null, as no image was set yet. After calling the method expecting not null.

      • doesMethodGetUsersWork

        public void doesMethodGetUsersWork()
        Comparing two lists, one created by calling method getUsers before adding user "testingDummy" into database and second created by calling the same method after adding the user. Expecting that lists do not equal. Calling method dropUser on user "testingDummy" at the end.

      • doesMethodToggleUserRole

        public void doesMethodToggleUserRole()
        Checks two String values of user's roles, one String before calling method toggleUserRole and another one after calling method toggleUserRole. Values should not equal when compared.
